<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  presentation-linkbase.xml

  Vendor-neutral, professional-grade scaffold for an XBRL 2.1 presentation
  linkbase. Demonstrates the canonical wiring expected by every regulator
  (SEC EDGAR, ESMA ESEF, FRC/HMRC, Dutch SBR/KvK/AFM, EBA COREP/FINREP, etc.).

  Authoritative sources:
    * XBRL 2.1 Recommendation, Section 5.2.4 (presentation linkbase) and
      Section 4 (Extended Links / Locators / Arcs):
      https://www.xbrl.org/Specification/XBRL-2.1/REC-2003-12-31/
      XBRL-2.1-REC-2003-12-31+corrected-errata-2013-02-20.html
    * XBRL Label Role Registry (LRR) v1.0:
      https://www.xbrl.org/lrr/lrr.xml

  STANDARD LABEL ROLES (XBRL 2.1, Section 5.2.2.2.2, all under
  http://www.xbrl.org/2003/role/):

    label                  Default human-readable label.
    terseLabel             Short form, omits redundant context.
    verboseLabel           Long form, includes full context.
    totalLabel             Used for a parent that totals its children.
    periodStartLabel       Used when displaying instant facts at the
                           start of a duration (opening balance).
    periodEndLabel         Used when displaying instant facts at the
                           end of a duration (closing balance).
    documentation          Concept documentation.
    definitionGuidance     Authoritative definition guidance.
    disclosureGuidance     Disclosure guidance.
    presentationGuidance   Presentation guidance.
    measurementGuidance    Measurement guidance.
    commentaryGuidance     Commentary guidance.
    exampleGuidance        Worked example.

  Note: netLabel is NOT a standard XBRL 2.1 role; it lives in the LRR
  (see below).

  LRR NEGATED LABEL and NET LABEL ROLES (under http://www.xbrl.org/2009/role/,
  status REC, authoritative schema negated-2009-12-16.xsd):

    negatedLabel
    negatedTerseLabel
    negatedTotalLabel
    negatedNetLabel
    negatedPeriodStartLabel
    negatedPeriodEndLabel

  And in http://www.xbrl.org/2009/role/ (separate LRR entry, REC):

    netLabel                 Used for net amounts (LRR, not 2003 standard).

  When a processor (Arelle, viewer, EDGAR renderer) sees a preferredLabel
  that is a negated label role on a presentation arc whose target is
  numeric, it MUST present the displayed value multiplied by minus one.
  The underlying XBRL fact value is unchanged; only the rendering flips.

  ORDER, USE AND PRIORITY (XBRL 2.1, Sections 3.5.3 and 4.11.1.3.1):

    order      xs:decimal. Determines display order of siblings under the
               same parent in a presentation tree. Per XBRL 2.1 sec.
               3.5.3.9.5 the order attribute is OPTIONAL (default 1).
               Uniqueness of order values among siblings is NOT a XBRL
               2.1 conformance requirement; it is a regulator FILING
               rule (e.g. EDGAR EFM, ESEF Reporting Manual) and good
               authoring practice. Order is NOT identity: changing it
               does not create a new arc.

    use        "optional" (default) or "prohibited". A prohibited arc
               with matching equivalence semantics suppresses an
               inherited arc from a base taxonomy.

    priority   xs:integer. Default is 0. When two equivalent arcs
               conflict (same source, target, arcrole, link role and
               attribute set other than use and priority), the arc with
               the HIGHER priority wins. At EQUAL priority, "prohibited"
               wins over "optional" (XBRL 2.1 sec. 3.5.3.9.7.5). This
               is the only supported override mechanism for taxonomy
               extensions.

  Override pattern (extension overrides a base taxonomy arc):
      1. Emit a prohibited arc with the same xlink:from, xlink:to,
         xlink:arcrole and link role as the inherited arc. Use a
         priority that is GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO the inherited
         arc's priority (at equal priority, prohibited still wins).
      2. Emit a new optional arc with the desired order / preferredLabel.

  Concept hrefs resolve to extension-schema.xsd (sibling file). Replace
  ext_ concepts with your taxonomy QNames before production use.
-->
<link:linkbase
    xmlns:link="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/linkbase"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/linkbase
                        http://www.xbrl.org/2003/xbrl-linkbase-2003-12-31.xsd">

  <!--
    roleRef declares the custom Extended Link Role (ELR) used below.
    The href MUST resolve to the link:roleType definition in the
    taxonomy schema (extension-schema.xsd) where the role is declared
    with usedOn = link:presentationLink.
  -->
  <link:roleRef
      roleURI="http://example.com/role/StatementOfFinancialPosition"
      xlink:type="simple"
      xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#StatementOfFinancialPosition"/>

  <!--
    presentationLink for the Statement of Financial Position ELR.
    Two level hierarchy:

      StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract  (root, abstract)
        Assets                              (parent of nested children)
          CurrentAssets                     (child)
          NoncurrentAssets                  (child)
        Liabilities                         (sibling of Assets)
        Equity                              (sibling)
        LiabilitiesAndEquity                (total, preferredLabel demo)

    The prohibition pattern is shown by emitting a prohibited arc
    (use="prohibited", priority="2") that suppresses an inherited
    Assets to Goodwill arc from a hypothetical base taxonomy.
  -->
  <link:presentationLink
      xlink:type="extended"
      xlink:role="http://example.com/role/StatementOfFinancialPosition">

    <!-- Locators (one per concept referenced by an arc) -->

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"
        xlink:label="loc_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_Assets"
        xlink:label="loc_Assets"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_CurrentAssets"
        xlink:label="loc_CurrentAssets"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_NoncurrentAssets"
        xlink:label="loc_NoncurrentAssets"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_Liabilities"
        xlink:label="loc_Liabilities"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_Equity"
        xlink:label="loc_Equity"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_LiabilitiesAndEquity"
        xlink:label="loc_LiabilitiesAndEquity"/>

    <link:loc
        xlink:type="locator"
        xlink:href="extension-schema.xsd#ext_Goodwill"
        xlink:label="loc_Goodwill"/>

    <!-- Level 1: Abstract root to top-level sections -->

    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"
        xlink:to="loc_Assets"
        order="1.0"
        use="optional"/>

    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"
        xlink:to="loc_Liabilities"
        order="2.0"
        use="optional"/>

    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"
        xlink:to="loc_Equity"
        order="3.0"
        use="optional"/>

    <!--
      Total row using the STANDARD totalLabel role. Renderers display
      the concept's totalLabel-roled label here ("Total liabilities and
      equity") instead of the default label.
    -->
    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"
        xlink:to="loc_LiabilitiesAndEquity"
        order="4.0"
        preferredLabel="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/role/totalLabel"
        use="optional"/>

    <!-- Level 2: Assets to nested children (demonstrates nesting) -->

    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_Assets"
        xlink:to="loc_CurrentAssets"
        order="1.0"
        use="optional"/>

    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_Assets"
        xlink:to="loc_NoncurrentAssets"
        order="2.0"
        use="optional"/>

    <!--
      LRR negatedLabel demonstration. The Equity branch is also
      presented with sign flipped under a different ordering, e.g. when
      stacking an "outflow" view. The fact's stored value is unchanged;
      only the rendered number is multiplied by minus one, and the label
      assigned the negatedLabel role on the concept is shown.

      Note: order 3.5 keeps it visually distinct from the order=3.0 sibling
      above. Per XBRL 2.1 sec. 3.5.3.9.5 sibling order uniqueness is not a
      spec requirement, but most regulator filing rules (EDGAR EFM, ESEF)
      require unique sibling order values; treat them as if they must be
      distinct.

      The two arcs (order=3.0 with no preferredLabel, order=3.5 with
      preferredLabel=negatedLabel) are NOT equivalent under XBRL 2.1
      sec. 3.5.3.9.7.4 because preferredLabel differs, so no priority is
      needed to keep them both alive. The priority attribute is therefore
      omitted here . it would be a no-op anyway.
    -->
    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_StatementOfFinancialPositionAbstract"
        xlink:to="loc_Equity"
        order="3.5"
        preferredLabel="http://www.xbrl.org/2009/role/negatedLabel"
        use="optional"/>

    <!--
      Prohibition pattern. Demonstrates how an extension taxonomy
      SUPPRESSES an inherited arc from a base taxonomy. The hypothetical
      inherited arc is:

          Assets parent-child Goodwill   priority="0"  use="optional"

      To remove it, we emit an arc with identical equivalence relevant
      attributes (xlink:from, xlink:to, xlink:arcrole, link role) but
      with use="prohibited" and a HIGHER priority. The conflict
      resolution rule (XBRL 2.1 Section 3.5.3) selects the prohibited
      arc, which causes processors to drop the relationship entirely.
    -->
    <link:presentationArc
        xlink:type="arc"
        xlink:arcrole="http://www.xbrl.org/2003/arcrole/parent-child"
        xlink:from="loc_Assets"
        xlink:to="loc_Goodwill"
        order="99.0"
        priority="2"
        use="prohibited"/>

  </link:presentationLink>
</link:linkbase>
